Here is another idea:  append the 'home' domain to any domain name
that doesn't contain a period.  For example, the host name 'ucb-arpa'
would be expanded into 'ucb-arpa.berkeley.arpa' if the home domain
were 'berkeley.arpa', while a host name like 'hou3c.att.uucp' would
be left unchanged.

If this approach is used, addresses in which a user name appears
directly under a top level domain name will cause problems, because
an address like 'user@edu' will be transformed into 'user@edu.berk-
eley.arpa'.  Is it safe to assume that such addresses will not occur
in practice?
				Kenneth Almquist

